.START 

Arx Inc. agreed to acquire Comstron Corp., a Melville, N.Y., manufacturer of frequency-control products, for $8 million plus additional payments for three years based on performance. 

Closely held Comstron's products are used in radar and other systems. 

Arx designs and makes electronic and magnetic products, and mechanical systems used in spacecraft and military vehicles.
Arx also provides engineering services to the government and holds 70% of VTX Electronics Corp., a Farmingdale, N.Y., distributor of wire and cable products. 

